data.name: Oricorio

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. It uses ethereal dance steps to call forth the spirits of the dead.

data.name: Lillie's Cutiefly

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: When it senses the auras of people or Pokémon who are having fun, it will draw close and give them a painful poke with its long proboscis.

data.name: Lillie's Ribombee

abilities.name: Inviting Wink
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand and you put any number of Basic Pokémon you find there onto their Bench.

data.flavorText: Ribombee can sense when people or Pokémon are feeling down, and it will cheer them up with handmade pollen puffs.

data.name: Lillie's Comfey

attacks.name: Inviting Flowers
attacks.text: You may search your deck for any number of Basic Lillie's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Fade Out
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

data.flavorText: It uses its vine to pick flowers. The flowers that Comfey attaches to itself develop healing properties.

data.name: Mimikyu ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Mischievous Hands
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon and put 3 damage counters on each of them.

attacks.name: Ghostly Trip
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.name: Dhelmise

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

data.flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

data.name: Impidimp
data.flavorText: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.

data.name: Morgrem
data.flavorText: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It's popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.

data.name: Grimmsnarl

attacks.name: Shadowy Knot
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

data.flavorText: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn't given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.

data.name: Milcery
data.flavorText: When attacked, it tackles its foe and covers them in cream. With its foe either blinded or astonished by deliciousness, Milcery flees.

data.name: Alcremie ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Confectionary Gift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

data.name: Cubone
data.flavorText: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

data.name: Swinub

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn't give it any trouble.

data.name: Piloswine
data.flavorText: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is resistant to the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.

data.name: Mamoswine ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Mammoth Hauler
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Rumbling March
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Stage 2 Pokémon on your Bench.

data.name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

data.name: Pupitar

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

data.name: Regirock

abilities.name: Rock Armor
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Breaching Lariat
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

data.flavorText: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon's rock body, but nothing was found—not even a brain or a heart.

data.name: Pancham

attacks.name: Focus Fist
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Wanting to make sure it's taken seriously, Pancham's always giving others a glare. But if it's not focusing, it ends up smiling.

data.name: Rockruff

attacks.name: Dig It Up
attacks.text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may discard that card.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is very friendly when it's young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

data.name: Lycanroc

abilities.name: Spike-Clad
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Spiky Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Clamping Fangs
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

data.name: Hop's Silicobra

attacks.name: Turf Maker
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: Silicobra's neck pouch, which can inflate and deflate like a balloon, gets more elastic each time Silicobra sheds its skin.

data.name: Hop's Sandaconda

attacks.name: Rumble
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Break Ground
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It will expand its body as much as it can and then contract itself, blasting out sand with enough force to wash away a dump truck.

data.name: Toedscool
data.flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

data.name: Toedscruel

abilities.name: Secret Forest Path
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, your Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost is ColorlessColorless less.

data.flavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.

data.name: Klawf

attacks.name: Snipping Pincers
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

data.name: Koffing
data.flavorText: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

data.name: Weezing

attacks.name: Pervasive Gas
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Crazy Blast
attacks.text: If this Pokémon used Pervasive Gas during your last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

data.name: Paldean Wooper

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: It's dangerous for Wooper to travel alone. They line up in groups of three or four and help each other as they walk around the wetlands.

data.name: Paldean Clodsire ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Poison Ring
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Giga Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Tyranitar

abilities.name: Daunting Gaze
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Item cards from their hand.

attacks.name: Cracking Stomp
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

data.name: N's Purrloin

attacks.name: Thieving Swipe
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand, and you choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of their deck.

data.flavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

data.name: N's Zorua
data.flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

data.name: N's Zoroark ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Trade
abilities.text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Night Joker
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your Benched N's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

data.name: Pangoro

attacks.name: Torment
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

attacks.name: Power Tackle
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.

data.name: Lokix
data.flavorText: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can't stay in this mode for long.

data.name: Bombirdier

attacks.name: Drop Shot
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

data.name: Escavalier

attacks.name: Iron Buster
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch'd.

data.name: N's Klink

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

data.name: N's Klang

attacks.name: Spinning Gears
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.

data.name: N's Klinklang

attacks.name: Triple Smash
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 120 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

data.name: Galarian Stunfisk

attacks.name: Bounding Bite
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

data.name: Magearna

abilities.name: Auto Heal
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, heal 90 damage from that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

data.flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

data.name: Hop's Corviknight

attacks.name: Shoot Through
attacks.text: This attack also does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Steel Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 60 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.

data.name: Cufant
data.flavorText: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.

data.name: Copperajah
data.flavorText: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.

data.name: Hop's Zacian ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Insta-Strike
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Brave Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Brave Slash.

data.name: Bagon

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.

data.name: Shelgon

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.

data.name: Salamence ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Wide Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Dragon Impact
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Druddigon

attacks.name: Dragon's Fury
attacks.text: Attach a Basic Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Dragon Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

data.name: N's Reshiram

attacks.name: Powerful Rage
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

data.name: Hop's Snorlax

abilities.name: Extra Helpings
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Hop's Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Extra Helpings doesn't stack.

attacks.name: Dynamic Press
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 80 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: This gluttonous Pokémon eats constantly, apart from when it's asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.

data.name: Sentret
data.flavorText: This Pokémon is extremely cautious. Its supple tail is well muscled and firm to the touch.

data.name: Furret
data.flavorText: It raises its offspring inside a long, narrow nest. Once they're old enough, it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.

data.name: Dunsparce

attacks.name: Trading Places
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

data.name: Dudunsparce ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Tenacious Tail
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon ex in play.

attacks.name: Destructive Drill
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Kecleon

attacks.name: Stealth Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long, it will pout and never reveal itself.

data.name: Tropius

attacks.name: Fruit Bearing
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.

data.flavorText: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

data.name: Audino

attacks.name: Beckon
attacks.text: Put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand.

data.flavorText: Audino's sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino's ears.

data.name: Minccino
data.flavorText: These Pokémon like things neat and tidy. They are always sweeping and dusting their habitat, using their tails as brooms.

data.name: Cinccino
data.flavorText: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.

data.name: Noibat

attacks.name: Rapid Draw
attacks.text: Draw a card.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

data.name: Noivern

abilities.name: Tuning Echo
abilities.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, ignore all Energy in the cost of Frightening Howl used by this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Frightening Howl
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Ultrasonic waves emitted by a Noivern can pulverize a large boulder. This Pokémon has a cruel disposition.

data.name: Komala

attacks.name: Slumbering Smack
attacks.text: Both Active Pokémon are now Asleep. During your next turn, attacks used by this Pokémon do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.

data.name: Drampa
data.flavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

data.name: Skwovet

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

data.flavorText: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.

data.name: Greedent

attacks.name: Gluttonous Tail
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

data.name: Hop's Rookidee

attacks.name: Intimidating Stare
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee's wings, it'll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.

data.name: Hop's Corvisquire
data.flavorText: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.

data.name: Hop's Wooloo
data.flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

data.name: Hop's Dubwool

abilities.name: Defiant Horn
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

data.flavorText: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

data.name: Cramorant

attacks.name: Ceaseless Spitting
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It's an incredibly poor learner because it uses the bare minimum amount of energy for its brain. It focuses on battling instead.

data.name: Hop's Cramorant

attacks.name: Fickle Spitting
attacks.text: If your opponent doesn't have exactly 3 or 4 Prize cards remaining, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Cramorant instinctively swallow everything whole. They're at their most formidable when they're struggling to swallow overly large prey.

data.name: Lechonk
data.flavorText: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.

data.name: Oinkologne

attacks.name: Aromatic Stomps
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: This is a meticulous Pokémon that likes to keep things tidy. It shrouds itself in a floral aroma that soothes the Pokémon around it.

data.name: Squawkabilly

attacks.name: Add On
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

data.flavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they're out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

data.name: Maractus

abilities.name: Exploding Needles
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

data.flavorText: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

data.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Frigid Fluttering
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

data.name: Wailord

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

data.name: Iono's Kilowattrel

abilities.name: Flashing Draw
abilities.text: You must discard a Basic Lightning Energy from this Pokémon in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

data.flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

data.name: Yanma

attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: As Yanma surveys its territory, it periodically stops to hover in place by flapping its wings at high speeds.

data.name: Pineco
data.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

data.name: Shroomish
data.flavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

data.name: Breloom

attacks.name: Damage Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

data.name: Cynthia's Roselia
data.flavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

data.name: Cynthia's Roserade

abilities.name: Cheer On to Glory
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Cynthia's Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

data.name: Mow Rotom

attacks.text: Discard a Stadium in play.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

data.flavorText: The lawn mower is one of the household appliances that led to the development of the Rotom Dex.

data.name: Shaymin

abilities.name: Flower Curtain
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon that don't have a Rule Box by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)

data.flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

data.name: Dwebble

attacks.name: Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

data.name: Crustle

attacks.name: Superb Scissors
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.

data.name: Fomantis
data.flavorText: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

data.name: Lurantis

attacks.name: Petal Blade Dance
attacks.text: Discard 2 Basic Grass Energy cards from your hand. If you can't discard 2 cards in this way, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

data.name: Team Rocket's Blipbug

attacks.name: Searching Eyes

data.flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

data.name: Applin

attacks.name: Mini Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple's skin and prevent it from rotting.

data.name: Dipplin

attacks.name: Energy Loop
attacks.text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

data.flavorText: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.

data.name: Hydrapple

attacks.name: Hydra Breath
attacks.text: Discard 6 Basic Grass Energy cards from your hand, and Knock Out your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you can't discard 6 cards in this way, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Seven syrpents live inside an apple made of syrup. The syrpent in the center is the commander.

data.name: Team Rocket's Tarountula

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon's natural enemy.

data.flavorText: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

data.name: Smoliv
data.flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

data.name: Dolliv

attacks.name: Nutrients

data.flavorText: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur to cause huge explosions.

data.name: Ethan's Slugma
data.flavorText: Its lava body can cool and chip away at times, but a magma bath will heal it right up.

data.flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Searing Flame

data.flavorText: This form is the most aggressive, bombarding enemies with the intensity of flames blazing within a hearth.

abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may discard the bottom card of your deck. If you do, discard all cards from this Pokémon and put this Pokémon on top of your deck.

data.flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

data.name: Misty's Staryu

attacks.name: Bubble Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

data.name: Misty's Starmie

attacks.name: Abrupt Flash
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved from Misty's Staryu during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

data.name: Misty's Magikarp

abilities.name: So Submerged
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

data.name: Misty's Gyarados

attacks.name: Splashing Panic
attacks.text: Discard the top 7 cards of your deck, and this attack does 70 damage for each Misty's Pokémon that you discarded in this way.

data.flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

data.name: Misty's Lapras

attacks.name: Swim Together
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Misty's Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.

data.name: Team Rocket's Articuno

abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to your Basic Team Rocket's Pokémon. (Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)

attacks.name: Dark Frost
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Team Rocket's Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

data.name: Cynthia's Feebas

attacks.name: Undulate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.

data.name: Cynthia's Milotic

attacks.name: Aqua Split
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

data.name: Clamperl

attacks.name: Shell Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Clamperl's pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder's pearls.

data.flavorText: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

data.name: Gorebyss

attacks.name: Crescendo Wave

data.flavorText: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

data.name: Buizel
data.flavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Aqua Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

data.name: Snover
data.flavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

data.name: Abomasnow

attacks.name: Frozen Wood
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has 2 or more Grass Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

data.name: Wash Rotom

attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

data.name: Arrokuda

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.name: Cetoddle

attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Team Rocket's Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Team Rocket's Ampharos

abilities.name: Darkest Impulse
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent plays a Pokémon from their hand to evolve 1 of their Pokémon, put 4 damage counters on that Pokémon. The effect of Darkest Impulse doesn't stack.

data.flavorText: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

data.name: Electrike
data.flavorText: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

data.name: Manectric

attacks.name: Flash Impact
attacks.text: This attack also does 40 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

data.name: Rotom

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

data.name: Zeraora

attacks.name: Thunder Raid
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack does 210 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon ex. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

data.name: Team Rocket's Drowzee

attacks.name: Hypnotic Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.

data.name: Team Rocket's Hypno

attacks.name: Bench Manipulation
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a coin for each of their Benched Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon for each tails. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

data.flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

data.name: Team Rocket's Mewtwo ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Power Saver
abilities.text: This Pokémon can't attack unless you have 4 or more Team Rocket's Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Erasure Ball
attacks.text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from your Benched Pokémon. This attack does 60 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.name: Team Rocket's Wobbuffet

attacks.name: Rocket Mirror
attacks.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Team Rocket's Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

data.name: Steven's Baltoy

attacks.name: Summoning Sign
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Steven's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

data.name: Steven's Claydol

attacks.name: Eerie Light
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Clay Blast
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

data.name: Team Rocket's Chingling

attacks.name: Chiming Commotion
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

data.flavorText: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

data.name: Steven's Carbink

abilities.name: Stone Palace
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, all of your Steven's Pokémon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Stone Palace doesn't stack.

data.flavorText: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

data.name: Team Rocket's Mimikyu

attacks.name: Gemstone Mimicry
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Tera Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

data.name: Team Rocket's Dottler

attacks.name: Disruptive Radar
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.

data.flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

data.name: Team Rocket's Orbeetle

abilities.name: Rocket Brain
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Team Rocket's Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

data.name: Mankey

attacks.name: Wild Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Drag Off
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. This attack does 30 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

data.name: Annihilape

abilities.name: Lose Cool
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has 2 or more damage counters on it, attacks used by this Pokémon do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Impact Blow
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Impact Blow.

data.flavorText: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

data.name: Ethan's Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Try to Imitate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

data.flavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

data.name: Team Rocket's Larvitar

attacks.name: Mountain Munch
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

data.name: Team Rocket's Pupitar

attacks.name: Explosive Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

data.name: Team Rocket's Tyranitar

abilities.name: Sand Stream
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, put 2 damage counters on each of your opponent's Basic Pokémon.

attacks.name: Demolition Tackle
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

data.name: Nosepass
data.flavorText: The magnet in Nosepass's nose provides an unerring compass, making this Pokémon an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

data.name: Probopass

attacks.name: Mountain Drop
attacks.text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 70 more damage.

data.flavorText: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack a foe from three directions.

data.name: Meditite

attacks.name: Steady Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

data.name: Medicham

attacks.name: Harmonious Spirit Palm
attacks.text: If this Pokémon and your opponent's Active Pokémon have the same amount of Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

data.name: Regirock ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Regi Charge
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Giant Rock
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Stage 2 Pokémon, this attack does 140 more damage.

data.name: Cynthia's Gible

attacks.name: Rock Hurl
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

data.flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

data.name: Cynthia's Gabite

abilities.name: Champion's Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Cynthia's Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

data.name: Cynthia's Garchomp ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Corkscrew Dive
attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Draconic Buster
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Hippopotas

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.

data.name: Hippowdon

attacks.name: Super Sandstorm
attacks.text: This attack also does 40 damage to each Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

data.name: Mudbray

attacks.name: Running Charge
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won't dry out even if it's exposed to the sun for a long time.

data.name: Mudsdale

abilities.name: Mud Coat
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

data.name: Arven's Toedscool

attacks.name: Slight Intrusion
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

data.name: Arven's Toedscruel

attacks.name: Pull
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

data.name: Cornerstone Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Rock Kagura
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Fighting Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Mountain Ramming
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: This form has excellent defenses, absorbing impacts solidly like the cornerstones that support houses.

data.name: Team Rocket's Ekans

attacks.name: Drag Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however.

data.name: Team Rocket's Arbok

abilities.name: Potent Glare
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Pokémon that has an Ability from their hand, except for Team Rocket's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spinning Tail
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidoran♀

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidorina

attacks.name: Dark Awakening
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 of your Darkness Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Love Impact
attacks.text: If a Pokémon that has "Nidoking" in its name is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.flavorText: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidoran♂
data.flavorText: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it's friendly with.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidorino

attacks.name: Horn Rend
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

data.flavorText: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

data.name: Team Rocket's Nidoking ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Tainted Horn
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 8 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

data.name: Team Rocket's Zubat

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

data.flavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun's light won't reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

data.name: Team Rocket's Golbat

abilities.name: Sneaky Bite
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

data.name: Team Rocket's Crobat ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Biting Spree
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon and put 2 damage counters on each of them.

attacks.name: Assassin's Return
attacks.text: You may put this Pokémon into your hand. (Discard all cards attached to this Pokémon.)

data.name: Team Rocket's Grimer

attacks.name: Corrosive Sludge
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, discard the Defending Pokémon and all attached cards.

data.flavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

data.name: Team Rocket's Muk

attacks.name: Gooped Up
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Hazardous Venom
attacks.text: This attack does 100 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It's thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
